  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This page is to summarize how to use timer for OS."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Arm generic timer"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Arm architecture provides the following timers"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "headers": [
        "Timer",
        "When is the timer present?"
      ],
      "rows": [
        [
          "EL1 physical timer",
          "Always"
        ],
        [
          "EL1 virtual timer",
          "Always"
        ],
        [
          "Non-secure EL2 physical timer",
          "Implements EL2 and Non-secure state"
        ],
        [
          "Non-secure EL2 virtual timer",
          "Implements FEAT_VHE and Non-secure state"
        ],
        [
          "Secure EL2 physical timer",
          "Implements FEAT_SEL2"
        ],
        [
          "Secure EL2 virtual timer",
          "Implements FEAT_SEL2"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We are going to use EL1 physical timer (Generic timer) for the RTA-OS functionality"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The Cortex RR52 processor does not include the system counter. This resides in the SoC. The system counter value is distributed to the Cortex®-R52 processor with a synchronous binary encoded 64-bit bus, CNTVALUEB[63:0]."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/3.0%20SAIL%20RTA-OS%20Timer%20settings/SAIL_Os_Timer_Architecture.jpg?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/3.0 SAIL RTA-OS Timer settings/SAIL_Os_Timer_Architecture.jpg"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Configuring the timer for OS interrupt"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We configured OS counter as Software in RTA-OS tool. Which means we need to call Os_IncrementCounter_SystemTimer_Cx (X = 0, 1 and 2) for thh respective Core timer ISR"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "And one tick is 1ms, so we the timer to generate an interrupt for 1ms"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/3.0%20SAIL%20RTA-OS%20Timer%20settings/image-2024-10-28_10-53-26.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/3.0 SAIL RTA-OS Timer settings/image-2024-10-28_10-53-26.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In the StartupHook, we will configure the timer compare value CNTP_CVAL by reading the current counter value CNTPCT and adding the value equal to 1ms"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Read the current timer value (CNTPCT)",
        "Add an 1ms to current counter value",
        "Now configure this value in CNTP_CVAL",
        "When timer reaches the CNTP_CVAL, we will get an ISR in respective Core."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "System counter for 1ms = 18750, we got this value from ETAS code. We need to find which document from Qualcomm gives this value."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Whenever the GenericCounter_ISR occurs we need to reset the CNTP_CVAL as given in above steps."
    }
  ],
